IEListener
public class IEEventListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements net.sf.jiffie.WindowListener, net.sf.jiffie.NavigationListener

The IEEventListener acts as a control instance for InternetExplorer instances created and used by any IEFunctionTag

target

protected net.sf.jiffie.InternetExplorer target
The browser to which this event listener is listening to

browsers

protected BrowserCache browsers
The list of open browser windows. The listener has to take care to add new browser windows to that list and to remove them again on close.

Constructor Detail

IEEventListener

public IEEventListener()
Deafult constructor. Currently does nothing

IEEventListener

public IEEventListener(net.sf.jiffie.InternetExplorer target,
                       BrowserCache browserCache)
Instantiates a new listener and adds itself as navigation listener and window listener to the given browser. Additionally adds the given browser to the list of all open browser windows.

Parameters:
target - The browser to watch
browserCache - The list of all open browser windows

onQuit

public void onQuit()
On closing a browser window we've to clean up. This method releases the COM object of the browser and removes it from the list of open browser windows.
